Hi Maria, 

I have had a look into this, it is quite odd! Are you using an SEO/SEM company, as they may be best to provide some advice on this. If not, I can look into it further for you, we would probably look to integration Google Analytics with your WooCommerce using a different plugin and see if that does the trick. My best guess at this point would be it's due to either the way the products are setup/being sold (the build your own box is quite unique and GA may not be picking up 100% of the transactions), there has been a custom 'thank-you' page or tracking code implemented that is blocking this data from transferring. 

Either way I wouldn't rely on the GA reports for financial data etc as they are not 100% full proof if that makes sense. You are best to use the WooCommerce reporting feature. Let me know if there is an Agency involved still?
